<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB07936</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT TO MANAGE MEDICAL RESIDENCY TRAINING PROGRAMS IN THE PHILIPPINES</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Seeks to create the Philippine Medical Accreditation Council (PMAC) as attached agency of the DOH to ensure the quality of medical residency training for all specialties and sub-specialties of medical residents;
Provides for the roles and functions of the PMAC to include among others: 
Sets the standards of said training and ensure that they are at par with international standards such as the World Federation for Medical Education (WFME); 
Screens foreign graduates of medicine who will be trained and assess the equivalence of their basic medical education to the Philippine curriculum standard;
Includes provision on accreditation, curriculum, qualifications of applicants and general conditions for foreign medical graduates; Also incorporates provisions on working conditions, salaries and benefits, professional conduct of medical residents.
</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>VILLAFUERTE, LUIS RAYMUND JR. F.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2018-07-19</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON HEALTH ON 2018-07-30</td></tr></table>